ion.com/does-the-bible-say-pi-equals-3</ref>||2||0\n|-\n|434 BCE||[[Anaxagoras]] attempted to [[squaring the circle|square the circle]]<ref>https://www.math.rutgers.edu/~cherlin/History/Papers2000/wilson.html</ref>\n|[[compass and straightedge]]||Anaxagoras didn't offer any solution||0\n|-\n|c. 250 BCE||[[Archimedes]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{frac|223|71}} &lt; {{pi}} &lt; {{frac|22|7}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.140845...&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;{{pi}}&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;3.142857...||'''2'''\n|-\n|15 BCE||[[Vitruvius]]<ref name=\"Agarwal\"/>\n|{{frac|25|8}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.125||1\n|-\n|between 1 and 5||[[Liu Xin (scholar)|Liu Xin]]<ref name=\"Agarwal\"/><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_1AsFyM0d84C|title=\u4e2d\u897f\u6578\u5b78\u53f2\u7684\u6bd4\u8f03|last=\u8d99\u826f\u4e94|date=22 January 1991|publisher=\u81fa\u7063\u5546\u52d9\u5370\u66f8\u9928|isbn=9789570502688|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref name=\"needham volume 3 100\">Needham, Joseph (1986). ''Science and Civilization in China: Volume 3, Mathematics and the Sciences of the Heavens and the Earth''. Taipei: Caves Books, Ltd. Volume 3, 100.</ref>\n|Unknown method giving a figure for a [[Jialiang]] which [[Liu Xin (scholar)#Calculation of pi (\u03c0)|implies a value for {{pi}}]] \u03c0 \u2248 {{frac|162|({{radic|50}}+0.095)<sup>2</sup>}}.\n|align=\"right\"|3.1547...||1\n|-\n|130||[[Zhang Heng]] ([[Book of the Later Han]])<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{radic|10}} = 3.162277...<br />{{frac|736|232}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.1622...||1\n|-\n|150||[[Ptolemy]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{frac|377|120}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.141666...||'''3'''\n|-\n|250||[[Wang Fan]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{frac|142|45}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.155555...||1\n|-\n|263||[[Liu Hui's \u03c0 algorithm|Liu Hui]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|3.141024 &lt; {{pi}} &lt; 3.142074<br />{{frac|3927|1250}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.1416||'''3'''\n|-\n|400||[[:zh:\u4f55\u627f\u5929 (\u5357\u671d)|He Chengtian]]<ref name=\"Agarwal\"/>\n|{{frac|111035|35329}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.142885...||2\n|-\n|480||[[Zu Chongzhi]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|3.1415926 &lt; {{pi}} &lt; 3.1415927 <br />\n|align=\"right\"|3.1415926||'''7'''\n|-\n|499||[[Aryabhata]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{frac|62832|20000}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.1416||4<ref name=\"round\">Rounded to the nearest decimal.</ref>\n|-\n|640||[[Brahmagupta]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|{{radic|10}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.162277...||1\n|-\n|800||[[Al Khwarizmi]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|\n|align=\"right\"|3.1416||4<ref name=\"round\"/>\n|-\n|1150||[[Bh\u0101skara II]]<ref name=\"Agarwal\"/>\n| {{frac|3927|1250}} and {{frac|754|240}}\n|align=\"right\"|3.1416||4<ref name=\"round\"/>\n|-\n|1220||[[Leonardo of Pisa|Fibonacci]]<ref name=\"Bailey\"/>\n|\n|align=\"right\"|3.141818||3\n|-\n|1320|| [[Zhao Youqin's \u03c0 algorithm|Zhao Youqin]]<ref name=\"Agarwal\"/>\n|\n|align=\"right\"|3.141592||6\n|}\n\n== 1400-1949 ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"| Date\n!align=\"left\"| Who\n!align=\"left\"| Note\n!align=\"right\"| Decimal&nbsp;places<br />{{nowrap| ([[world record]]s in '''bold''') }}\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;background:lightblue;\"|''All records from 1400 onwards are given as the number of correct decimal places''.\n|-\n|1400||[[Madhava of Sangamagrama]]\n|Discovered the infinite [[power series]] expansion of {{pi}}, <br />now known as the [[Leibniz formula for \u03c0|Leibniz formula for pi]]<ref>{{cite journal| first=A. K.| last=Bag| year=1980| title=Indian Literature on Mathematics During 1400\u20131800 A.D.| journal=Indian Journal of History of Science| volume=15| issue=1| page=86| url=http://www.insa.nic.in/writereaddata/UpLoadedFiles/IJHS/Vol15_1_10_AKBag.pdf|quote={{pi}} \u2248 2,827,433,388,233/9\u00d710<sup>\u221211</sup> = 3.14159 26535 92222\u2026, good to 10 decimal places.}}</ref>\n|align=\"right\"|'''10'''\n|-\n|1424||[[Jamsh\u012bd al-K\u0101sh\u012b]]<ref>approximated 2\u03c0 to  9  sexagesimal  digits. ''Al-Kashi'', author: Adolf P. Youschkevitch, 